 Possible East German Foreign Policy -- tCHAPTER 17. Moscow, East Berlin and the "Hawks of Hadramawt" -- tAnnex -- tI. Bibliography -- tII. Archival Documents0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aRadical ideologies may manifest differently at first, but they do follow a similar logic: truth claims, promises of salvation and a unifying common enemy. In Yemen's transition process today, the secessionist movement Al-Hirak has summoned the spirit of South Yemen, the only Marxist state in Arabia. This book meticulously describes how East Germany supported the implantation of this alien ideology in Yemen through its policy of »Socialist state- and nation-building«. In the same breath, the analysis captures the GDR's activities in the Middle East and their vital role in Moscow's Cold War strategy. Last but least, the study provides one of the few compact overviews of East German foreign policy in the English language of today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCommunismzYemen, SouthxHistory. 0aSocialismzYemen, SouthxHistory. 4aArab Peninsula. 4aCold War. 4aContemporary History. 4aGDR. 4aIdeology. 4aInternational Relations. 4aMarxism. 4aMiddle East. 4aPolitical Ideologies. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPolitics. 4aSoviet Union. 4aState-Building. 4aState. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aArab Peninsula.  aCold War.  aContemporary History.  aGDR.  aIdeology.  aInternational Relations.  aMarxism.  aMiddle East.  aPolitical Ideologies.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aSoviet Union.  aState-Building.